params.name: data.org_display_name
params.description: Required. Name of the organization that the customer entity represents.

params.name: data.org_postal_address
params.description: Required. The organization address for the customer. To enforce US laws and embargoes, we require a region and zip code. You must provide valid addresses for every customer. To set the customer's language, use the Customer-level language code.

params.name: data.primary_contact_info
params.description: Primary contact info.

params.name: data.alternate_email
params.description: Secondary contact email. You need to provide an alternate email to create different domains if a primary contact email already exists. Users will receive a notification with credentials when you create an admin.google.com account. Secondary emails are also recovery email addresses. Alternate emails are optional when you create Team customers.

params.name: data.domain
params.description: Required. The customer's primary domain. Must match the primary contact email's domain.

params.description: Output only. Time when the customer was created.

params.name: data.update_time
params.description: Output only. Time when the customer was updated.

params.name: data.cloud_identity_id
params.description: Output only. The customer's Cloud Identity ID if the customer has a Cloud Identity resource.

params.name: data.language_code
params.description: Optional. The BCP-47 language code, such as "en-US" or "sr-Latn". For more information, see https://www.unicode.org/reports/tr35/#Unicode_locale_identifier.

params.description: Cloud Identity ID of the customer's channel partner. Populated only if a channel partner exists for this customer.
